We have lived near Salerno's for a year and it has been on our long list of places to try. We were so excited to order their takeout last night, and then incredibly let down by the food quality. The shrimp linguine was average at best, swimming in butter & minimally flavored. The chicken tenders were dry and the meat to breading ratio was disappointing. The pizza bread was hard, as if it had been sitting out for awhile or even reheated from a previous day...the cheese came entirely off with my first bite. This review is less meant to deter customers (hope that we caught the chef on a bad day!), but more to give a nudge to Salerno's to step up their game so we can rely on this great neighborhood joint for consistent quality & service. We want you guys to succeed!
